sql:
SELECT country_id, mp_num, shift_country
FROM sentiment_shifts
WHERE shift_country > 0;

SELECT DISTINCT p.name
FROM politicians p
INNER JOIN sentiments s ON p.politician_id = s.politician_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Map the emotional landscapes" is a metaphorical expression used to describe the process of gathering and summarizing sentiment data for a particular geographic area (countries in this case).; 
- "Genuine feelings" refers to the true sentiment expressed by individuals about politicians or countries.; 
- "Shift in perspectives" refers to a change in the way people view a particular country, which could be positive or negative.; 
- "Elasticity of sentiment" refers to how adaptable or resilient the sentiment is towards change.

Most recent sentiment data refers to the latest available sentiment data for each politician in each country; 
 Sentiment data includes perceived sentiment, true sentiment, shift, and stretch;
 The collection date refers to the date when the sentiment data was collected;
 Country shifts include the shift in sentiment and the stretch of sentiment towards each country;
 MPs refer to the members of parliament in each country.
